title: Jar And Cover, ca. 1820–30
provenance: Cecil Davis, LTD, 3 Grosvenor St, New Bond St, London, W.I., purchased (7-24-63) by WPW.
dimensions: H x diam.: 19 x 11 cm (7 1/2 x 4 5/16 in.)
description: Ovoid jar and cover on plain, short stem and square pedestal base all overs step cutting cover has notch for spoon. Mushroom finial with radial cutting.
